frameDefinitions: An Evaluee, which can be a person or an object, has an amount of acceptability or utilization based on general (often non-aesthetic) desirability.
A Searcher looks all over a Ground in order to find a Sought_entity.
An Agent acts to begin the life of a Process.
An Agent performs a series of unspecified tasks to plan for an Event to take place at a Scheduled_time and Place.
The Creator creates a new entity, the Created_entity, possibly out of Components.
An Agent schedules an Event to take place at a specified Scheduled_time and Place.
frameExamples: The newcomers <t>combed</t> the area looking for minerals
After discovering her knack for organization, she decided to try to  <t>launch</t> a career in human resources.
I've <t>arranged</t> a breakfast meeting for you tomorrow morning with Mr. Huntsberger.
The Libyans were <t>generating</t> arms for export.
Gina <t>scheduled</t> a dentist appointment for Monday in Berkeley.

This Frame Element marks expressions that indicate the process that the <fen>Agent</fen> initiates.

This role is for the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> initiates the <fen>Process</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Process</fen> is initiated.

The Creator creates a created entity.

The sentient being who schedules an <fen>Event</fen> to take place at a <fen>Time</fen> and <fen>Place</fen>.
